305
00:20:04,310 --> 00:20:06,020
I'll copy and pass them on to you all.

306
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:07,700
Of course,

307
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,980
for Director Lee, it will be in Braille.

308
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:30,290
Everyone,

309
00:20:32,150 --> 00:20:33,610
this is a codebook intercepted

310
00:20:33,630 --> 00:20:35,050
from Shanghai BIS.

311
00:20:36,150 --> 00:20:37,220
Though it's only half a volume,

312
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:39,940
I believe with this,

313
00:20:40,550 --> 00:20:43,220
your work efficiency
will be greatly improved.

314
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,050
With this,

315
00:20:58,550 --> 00:21:00,180
there shouldn't be much problem.

316
00:21:03,550 --> 00:21:04,290
Gentlemen,

317
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:06,770
the sooner we decipher their code,

318
00:21:07,110 --> 00:21:09,130
the sooner we can
grasp their intelligence.

319
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:10,900
Therefore,

320
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:14,370
the time given to you is limited.

321
00:21:14,830 --> 00:21:16,050
At most seven days.

322
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,180
Director Liang,

323
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,370
seven days?

324
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:23,980
Isn't that too short?

325
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:27,260
Seven days. That's too much to ask.

326
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:28,530
Exactly.

327
00:21:37,310 --> 00:21:39,260
Mr. Lee, do you want the manuscript?

328
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,180
The Japanese mean that

329
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,500
if we can't decipher

